	<body>
		<div class='white'></div>
		<table style="height: 100%;">
			<tr>
				<td id="nav" rowspan="2">
					<ul>
						<li>Home</li>
						<li>Projects</li>
					</ul>
				</td>
				<td id="header">
					<h1>
						Thomas Flucke
					</h1>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>
					<div id="content">
						<article>
							<p>
								Hello and welcome to my web site!  Since you are
								here, it's likely for one of the following reasons:
							</p>
							<ol style="list-style-type: upper-latin;">
								<li>
									I'm looking for some file/program I uploaded
									here.
								</li>
								<li>
									You're an employer looking for information
									about me.
								</li>
								<li>
									You're stalking me for some reason.
								</li>
							</ol>
							<p>
								If you are the later, I'm sorry there's not too
								much interesting here to look at.  Go follow
								somebody else.
							</p>
							<p>
								If you're an employer, welcome!  I am encoding
								a batch of fresh cookies as you read this.  They
								should arrive sometime after this technology
								actually exists.  If you are recruiting for a
								position that's working on making this possible,
								please hire me!  I would love the opportunity to
								work on something that could send fresh baked goods
								over the internet.
							</p>
							<p>
								This web site really only exists for my own purposes
								and amusement.  Nothing really all that important
								is on here.
						</p>
							<p>
								Regardless, I wouldn't publish this web site if I
								didn't want other people poking around so have fun
								exploring my life!
							</p>
						</article>
						<article>
							<img src="images/TomSeniorPhoto.png"
								style="max-width: 90%; max-height: 245px;
									   display: block; margin: 0 auto;" />
							<p>
								I'm presently studying Computer Science at Califonia
								Polytechnic State University in San Luis Obispo.  
								A university I chose to attend before considering
								how many times people would ask me its name.  As
								of Spring quarter 2016, I will be working a co-op
								at Livermore national labs as a software intern.
							</p>
							<p> 
								I'm a native of St. Louis, Missouri and I really
								only moved to California to try somewhere different
								from the place where I've lived my whole life.  
								Honestly not too sure where I plan to go after I
								graduate; I'll be evaluating my options and opinions
								on that soon.  In the mean time I'm gonna do what
								enjoy: writing programs and web sites.
							</p>
						</article>
						<article>
							
						</article>
